      },
      "lineNbr": 2741,
      "author": {
        "id": 1628636
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-02-07T20:26:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I actually just added the comment (and moved the code), the oldenv_copy mechanism was already there (see the restore part around line 2910), so I left it that way.\nNow, regardless of my patch, as to whether this is really needed or not, I\u0027m not sure this is the case either, as the fate of the minijail parent, after exec\u0027ing the child, is mainly to wait for it to exit, so having LD_PRELOAD set or unset in its env after forking would probably not change anything.\nBut I didn\u0027t remove it as I was under the assumption that it was there for a reason I might have missed.",
      "parentUuid": "775510e1_11253928",
